<style>
/* ── Workshop overrides (root-caused live in-browser, 2026-07-10 project-owner review) ─────────────
   Two theme↔content collisions, both fixed here rather than in the theme bundle. */

/* 1) Mermaid diagrams rendered ~300px in an 828px column (unreadable). Cause: the theme's
   .imageblock is display:flex, so the .mermaid div is a shrink-to-fit flex ITEM whose child
   svg is width:100% — circular sizing collapses to min-content. Give the item the full column. */
.doc .imageblock .mermaid { width: 100%; flex: 1 1 100%; }
/* mermaid's useMaxWidth caps each SVG at its NATURAL size, so simple diagrams (few nodes) still
   render tiny — unreadable, especially in the narrow (~45%) cockpit panel (project-owner review
   2026-07-11, M01 concept). Override the inline max-width so every diagram scales UP to fill the
   column, capped at 900px on the wide GH-Pages site and centered. viewBox keeps it proportional. */
.doc .imageblock .mermaid svg {
  width: 100% !important; max-width: 900px !important; height: auto !important;
  display: block; margin: 0 auto;
}

/* 2) Steps inside [tabs] panels rendered as overlapping black-bordered boxes. Cause: the
   theme ships tab-BAR styling with broad selectors (.tabs li / .tabs ul — it expects .tabs
   to be the bar element inside its own .tabset dialect), but the antora-tabs-extension
   classes the WHOLE openblock "tabs", so every content list in every PANEL got flex,
   height:2.5rem, border:1px solid black, bold, pointer. Neutralize inside panels only —
   the real bar (.tablist) keeps its styling. */
.openblock.tabs .tabpanel ul,
.openblock.tabs .tabpanel ol {
  display: block; flex-wrap: initial; list-style: revert; margin: revert; padding: revert;
}
.openblock.tabs .tabpanel li {
  display: list-item; align-items: initial; border: 0; cursor: auto; font-weight: inherit;
  height: auto; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0; padding: 0; position: static;
}
.openblock.tabs .tabpanel li + li { margin-top: revert; }
</style>
